      "term": "nudibranchia",
      "kind": "word",
      "cefrLevel": "C2",
      "senses": [
        {
          "pos": "noun",
          "definition": "a large group of soft-bodied, colorful sea slugs that have naked gills (nudibranchs) and usually live on the seafloor or among coral reefs",
          "examples": [
            "Marine biologists studied the diversity of nudibranchia in the coral reef.",
            "The aquarium featured a vivid display of nudibranchia."
          ],
          "collocations": [
            "species of nudibranchia",
